From: Andre Klapper <a9016009@gmx.de>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 12:19:05 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 43/50] Make PhutilExecChannel::write() return $this

Summary:
Static code analysis complains about
`./src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php:108: Method PhutilExecChannel::write() should return $this(PhutilExecChannel) but return statement is missing.`

Thus make `PhutilExecChannel::write()` return `$this`, like `PhutilChannelChannel` and shared parent `PhutilChannel` already do.

Test Plan: Run static code analysis.

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, mainframe98

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, mainframe98

Subscribers: tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26822
---
 src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php b/src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php
index 40a7cfda6c71..393e312e3ce8 100644
--- a/src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php
+++ b/src/channel/PhutilExecChannel.php
@@ -106,6 +106,7 @@ final class PhutilExecChannel extends PhutilChannel {
 
   public function write($bytes) {
     $this->future->write($bytes, $keep_pipe = true);
+    return $this;
   }
 
   public function closeWriteChannel() {
